  "prompt": "How can the life span of parakeet be increased?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to help increase a parakeet's lifespan:\n\n1. Proper diet\n- Provide a balanced diet with high-quality seeds, pellets, fresh fruits, and vegetables\n- Ensure fresh, clean water daily\n- Limit fatty seeds and treats\n\n2. Regular veterinary care\n- Annual check-ups with an avian veterinarian\n- Preventive health screenings\n- Prompt treatment of any health issues\n\n3. Clean living environment\n- Clean cage regularly\n- Maintain appropriate temperature and humidity\n- Provide adequate space and safe perches\n- Avoid drafts and extreme temperatures\n\n4. Mental and physical stimulation\n- Provide toys and activities\n- Allow out-of-cage playtime\n- Offer social interaction\n- Rotate toys to prevent boredom\n\n5. Reduce stress\n- Minimize loud noises\n- Maintain consistent routine\n- Provide a calm environment\n- Avoid sudden changes\n\n6. Proper hygiene\n- Regular bathing opportunities\n- Clean food and water dishes\n- Trim nails and beak as needed\n\n7. Avoid harmful substances\n- Keep away from toxic plants, fumes, and chemicals\n- Do not expose to cigarette smoke\n- Use safe cleaning products\n\nWith proper care, parakeets can live 10-15 years, sometimes even longer.",
